            "content": "{\n  \"files\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"apache/kafka\", \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/errors/TimeoutException.java\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"apache/kafka\", \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"apache/kafka\", \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/ProducerConfig.java\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"apache/kafka\", \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java\"}\n  ],\n  \"symbols\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"apache/kafka\", \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/errors/TimeoutException.java\", \"symbol\": \"TimeoutException\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"apache/kafka\", \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java\", \"symbol\": \"expiredBatches\"},\n    {\"repo\": \"apache/kafka\", \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/ProducerConfig.java\", \"symbol\": \"DELIVERY_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG\"}\n  ],\n  \"chain\": [\n    {\"repo\": \"apache/kafka\", \"path\": \"clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java\", \"symbol\": \"sendProducerData\"}\n  ],\n  \"text\": \"The Kafka producer timeout error 'Expiring N record(s) for topic-partition' is generated through the following components:\\n\\n1. **TimeoutException Class** (apache/kafka/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/common/errors/TimeoutException.java):\\n   - Defines the TimeoutException exception class that is thrown when records expire\\n   - Extends RetriableException, allowing for retry logic\\n\\n2. **Record Batch Expiration Logic** (apache/kafka/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/RecordAccumulator.java):\\n   - The expiredBatches(long now) method (line 465) determines which record batches have exceeded their delivery timeout\\n   - Iterates through all topic information and batches, checking if each batch has reached the delivery timeout using batch.hasReachedDeliveryTimeout(deliveryTimeoutMs, now)\\n   - Returns a list of expired batches that should be removed and failed\\n   - Uses the deliveryTimeoutMs property which is set from the delivery.timeout.ms configuration\\n\\n3. **Delivery Timeout Configuration** (apache/kafka/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/ProducerConfig.java):\\n   - Defines the DELIVERY_TIMEOUT_MS_CONFIG constant at line 165: 'delivery.timeout.ms'\\n   - This configuration controls the maximum time a record can remain in the producer before it is considered expired\\n   - Default value is 120 seconds (120 * 1000 milliseconds)\\n\\n4. **Error Message Generation** (apache/kafka/clients/src/main/java/org/apache/kafka/clients/producer/internals/Sender.java):\\n   - The sendProducerData method (line 357) orchestrates the expiration logic\\n   - Calls accumulator.expiredBatches(now) to get all expired batches\\n   - For each expired batch, creates an error message: 'Expiring ' + recordCount + ' record(s) for ' + topicPartition + ':' + time_elapsed_ms\\n   - Throws a new TimeoutException with this error message\\n   - This is where the user-facing error message originates\\n\\nThe flow is: delivery.timeout.ms config \u2192 RecordAccumulator.expiredBatches() checks timeout \u2192 Sender.sendProducerData() generates error \u2192 TimeoutException is thrown\"\n}\n",
